# Architecture Boundaries

- Keep dependency direction: `@excalidraw/common` -> `@excalidraw/math` -> `@excalidraw/element` -> `@excalidraw/excalidraw` -> `excalidraw-app`.
- Route editor state changes through actions/state abstractions; avoid ad hoc global stores in feature files.
- Keep app shell concerns in `excalidraw-app`; reusable editor logic belongs in `packages/excalidraw`.
- Avoid reverse imports from lower-level packages to higher-level app modules.

## How to verify

1. Run `yarn test:code` to catch existing restricted-import lint rules.
2. Check changed files and verify dependency direction manually when lint coverage is incomplete:
   - no `@excalidraw/excalidraw` imports inside `packages/common/**`, `packages/math/**`, or `packages/element/**`
   - no `excalidraw-app/**` imports from any `packages/**` module
3. Confirm new editor behavior is implemented in `packages/excalidraw` while app-shell wiring stays in `excalidraw-app`.
4. If violations recur, extend `no-restricted-imports` in `.eslintrc.json` to enforce the full chain automatically.
